# Backend Awareness

This project has a fixed backend requirements file at `BACKEND.md` (project root).

Whenever you make changes that affect the Laravel backend API — new endpoints, changed payloads, new database columns, new tables, changed auth flows — you MUST update `BACKEND.md` with:

1. The SQL migration (Section 1)
2. The endpoint reference (Section 2)
3. A changelog entry (Section 5) with date, description, frontend files, and backend impact

This keeps the backend team in sync without requiring them to read frontend code.

The file path is always: `BACKEND.md` at the workspace root.
